description: {"blocks":[{"key":"9gqct","text":"Cardiac tissue samples were obtained from human donors and sent to East Tennessee State University for processing. At ETSU, the tissue was dissected, sectioned with a cryostat, and stained for neuronal markers using the ABC IHC method. Pictures of the sections were obtained and analyzed for nerve density across different regions of the heart. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1s5i7","text":"Using the PAP Pen, carefully draw a water barrier circle around the tissue sections on the slide — allow this circle to dry for several seconds or up to approximately one minute.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b2ccd","text":"Rinse slides by placing them into a Coplin jar filled with PBS (pH 7.3 - 7.4): 4 x 5 min each","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8nt6a","text":"Place slides in 0.5% BSA + 0.4% Triton X-100 in PBS: 1 x 10 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2blcd","text":"Place slides in 1.0% H2O2 in PBS: 1 x 15 min. (2 ml of 30%  H2O2 in 60 ml of PBS)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":22,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":24,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":61,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":63,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1g9g9","text":"Place slides in PBS: 4 x 5 min each","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ercmk","text":"Place slides in 0.5% BSA + 0.4% Triton X-100 in PBS: 1 x 10 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6jnuo","text":"Remove slides one at a time and use a clean Kimwipe to wipe around the tissue sections to dry the slide. Keep the sections wet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"255d8","text":"Place the slides into a black, covered slide incubation box/humidity box","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"brl1m","text":"Cover the tissue sections with blocking buffer (150μl of normal goat serum (Jackson ImmunoResearch Laboratories, Cat. No. 005-000-121) OR normal rabbit serum (Jackson ImmunoResearch Laboratories, Cat. No. 011-000-120) + 10 mL of 1.0% BSA + 0.4% Triton X-100 in PBS)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e3vpn","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bl1hf","text":"Allow the sections to remain in blocking buffer for 1.5 - 2 hours at room temperature","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"e0ba0","text":"Pour off the blocking buffer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bkkbq","text":"Replace with primary antibody solution (antibody of choice diluted in the same blocking buffer used above)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1r64q","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"48m35","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ph3s","text":"Incubate overnight at room temperature","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bnnu1","text":"Place slides in PBS: 4 x 5 min each","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8qq13","text":"Place slides in 0.5% BSA + 0.4% Triton X-100 in PBS: 1 x 10 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bft0a","text":"While rinsing slides above, prepare the biotinylated secondary antibody solution. (Blocking buffer = 150μl of normal goat serum (Jackson ImmunoResearch Laboratories, Cat. No. 005-000-121) OR normal rabbit serum (Jackson ImmunoResearch Laboratories, Cat. No. 011-000-120) + 10 mL of 1.0% BSA + 0.4% Triton X-100 in PBS. Add 50μl of biotinylated secondary antibody to the blocking buffer solution.)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5tsam","text":"Cover the tissue with the secondary antibody solution and incubate for 2 hours at RT in the humidity box","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"atgqn","text":"Prepare the ABC reagent from the Vector Kit at least 30 min prior to using. ABC reagent is made by adding 1 drop of solution A + 1 drop of solution B to 2.5 mL of solution containing 1.0% BSA + 0.4% Triton-X 100 + PBS. Add solutions ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dibml","text":"A and B to the buffer in that order. Let this sit at RT while performing the following rinses.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ubsm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"as3na","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9k090","text":"Pour off the secondary antibody solution","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6u9d0","text":"Place slides in PBS: 4 x 5 min each","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4hg8g","text":"Place slides in 0.5% BSA + 0.4% Triton X-100 in PBS: 1 x 10 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"975qv","text":"Cover the tissue with the ABC reagent and incubate 1-1.5 hrs. in the humidity box","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4o438","text":"Prepare 50mM Tris buffer (Trizma, pH 7.6) for the next rinse stage — (1.49 g Trizma (pH 7.6, Sigma T7943) + 200 mL dH2O)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":117,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bs5ae","text":"Pour the ABC reagent off the slides","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1lk9d","text":"Place the slides in a Coplin jar with the Tris buffer: 2 x 10 mins.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6toqs","text":"During the last Tris buffer rinse, prepare the VIP development solution — must be at RT for proper use (Vector ImmPACT VIP Kit, SK4605). Use 5 mL VIP diluent + 3 drops of each of solutions 1, 2, 3, and 4 from the kit.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7l9je","text":"Place the slides onto a light-colored background to monitor color development.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ed8ei","text":"Add the VIP color development solution to the tissue sections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"encnf","text":"Monitor development of color, which should take from 2 to 20 min to reach maximum intensity. (Use a microscope to monitor.)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5896e","text":"Stop color development by submerging slides in dH2O in a Coplin jar","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":49,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ebeht","text":"Rinse with dH2O: 2 x 2 min each","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":13,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"ehud6","text":"Dehydrate the tissue","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7ib19","text":"rinse in 50% EtOH: 1x 2 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9p94l","text":"rinse in 75% EtOH: 1 x 2 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3r11e","text":"rinse in 95% EtOH: 2 x 2 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7qlv3","text":"rinse in 100% EtOH: 2 x 2 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7sjta","text":"rinse in Xylene: 2 x 5 min","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5s39t","text":"Attach coverslips using Cytoseal XYL (Thermo Scientific, Cat. No. 8312-4)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5v7mj","text":"Allow to air dry overnight","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"46hv5","text":"Image tissue sections using Olympus BX41 microscope equipped with an Olympus DP74 digital camera and cellSens software (Olympus America Inc., Center Valley, PA; RRID:SCR_016238)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c3201","text":"Stain sets 1, 2, and 3 of each tissue region with a different primary antibody: sheep anti-tyrosine hydroxylase (TH, Milipore Cat. No. AB1542, 1:500) or rabbit anti-tyrosine hydroxylase (TH, Pel-Freez Biologicals, Cat. No. P40101-150, 1:500), rabbit anti-vesicular acetylcholine transporter (VAChT, Synaptic Systems, Cat. No. 139103, 1:500), and rabbit anti-protein gene product 9.5 (PGP9.5, Abcam Cat. No. ab108986, 1:2000), respectively.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3raj1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"beka1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"25mr0","text":"Cut tissues into 30μm sections at -20 to -25°C using a Leica CM3050S cryostat (Leica Microsystems Inc., Bannockburn, IL, USA) ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1eau5","text":"Tissues shipped to ETSU at 4°C in a PBS solution containing 20% sucrose + 0.02% sodium azide","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1pssq","text":"Remove tissue samples from solution and dissect as needed, to isolate specific regions","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2rpsu","text":"Freeze tissues on dry ice and store at -80°C until ready to be sectioned","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dr56a","text":"Remove tissues from -80°C freezer and mount onto specimen plate using Tissue-Tek® O.C.T. Compound (Sakura Finetek USA, Cat. No. 4583)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bstio","text":"Collect sections on charged slides in a sequence that yields at least 4 sets of tissue sections per region of the heart, with each set spanning the entire thickness of the specimen","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1b8nu","text":"Store sets of tissues in slide boxes wrapped in aluminum foil at -20°C until further processing","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fsfjr","text":"Load slide onto stage and collect representative Z-stack images of each slide at 20X magnification. The Z-stack range is defined by the researcher as the furthest depth at which some nerves are still in focus, and the step size is determined by the program.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"517kq","text":"Leave set out to thaw at RT for 20 mins","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7trpk","text":"Save images as JPGs in groups sorted by specimen, region, and stain","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aj0en","text":"Record the nerve density percentage shown into a spreadsheet. Repeat the above adjustment until you have three consistent readings","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"21vj9","text":"Open desired JPG image within the ImageJ program","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fjbul","text":"Isolate and \"fill\" any high-contrast anomalies that should not be included in calculations","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"611vo","text":"Change image type to \"8-bit.\"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8um5b","text":"Adjust the threshold of the image until only the desired regions containing nerves are highlighted in red","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6obn8","text":"Calculate the average of the three readings","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4g358","text":"Input the average nerve density data (% area) into GraphPad Prism 8 for statistical analysis. Data should be separated by donor, heart region, and stain","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a4kfi","text":"Use the \"descriptive statistics\" function of the software to find the mean and standard deviation of each region","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ebcum","text":"Process each slide using EFI (extended focus image) to enhance Z-stack image.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cddi4","text":"Remove slides one at a time and use a clean Kimwipe to wipe around the tissue sections to dry the slide. Keep the sections wet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c5vrk","text":"Remove slides one at a time and use a clean Kimwipe to wipe around the tissue sections to dry the slide. Keep the sections wet.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"2sktl","text":"Tissues fixed in 4% paraformaldehyde in PBS at 4°C for 24 hrs","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
